Goal:
The purpose of this test is to test the evict operation from L1 cache to a higher cache level.

Details:
First we store some known value: 16-byte data = 0xa1a1_a1a1_a1a1_a1a1; 
and then perform Evict cache 1, to ensure that l1 is clean. 
In order to check that evict was performed correctly, we do an amoswapl, which should return from L2 returned the (dirty) data evicted from L1. After that we do a load from the same address and we should get the new data that was swapped from L2 after amoswapl.w.


